  <prompt>
    <goal>Replace the stub NOTES.md with substantive, Spaarke-specific commentary grounded in actual reading of the production code under src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/. Remove the `⚠️ STUB` banner only when both §1 (architecture fit) and §2 (how we build) have substance. NOTES.md is the most-cited file by the new skill — quality here determines whether the knowledge base actually changes agent output.</goal>
    <context>The existing NOTES.md is a structured stub with TODOs awaiting "Phase 4 senior engineer annotation pass" — this is that pass. The user asked Claude to act as a Senior AI Developer expert in both Agent Framework + Spaarke. NOTES.md must answer questions Claude will face when asked to extend SprkChatAgent or its middleware: where do Agent Framework primitives end and Spaarke patterns begin, what naming-clash gotchas exist, what middleware composition rules apply, what does the OTel pipeline look like, when reach for Agent Framework Workflows vs. JPS playbook engine vs. Foundry Agent Service.</context>
    <constraints>
      - NO fabrication — every claim about Spaarke code MUST be backed by a Read of the actual file (cite paths)
      - NO repeating upstream docs — NOTES.md is Spaarke-specific commentary, not a re-summary of /agents/ or /workflows/
      - The ⚠️ STUB banner is REMOVED only when both §1 and §2 have substantive content. Honest TODOs for what cannot yet be known (e.g., "first production use will reveal X") are acceptable
      - File path references MUST resolve — verify each path with Glob/Read before citing
      - Honor ADR-013 vocabulary: PublicContracts/ facade, AI Tool Framework (IAiToolHandler) vs Agent Framework tools, BFF-extension governance per .claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md
      - Keep total length ~150-250 lines (deep enough to be useful, not so deep it overflows the skill's load budget)
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
