  <steps>
    <step>Read SprkChatAgent.cs in full + SprkChatAgentFactory.cs + the 3 middleware files. Inventory: (a) what Agent Framework / Microsoft.Extensions.AI types are used and how, (b) the IChatClient wrapping pattern, (c) the UseFunctionInvocation vs raw-client split + why (compound intent detection per task 071), (d) the middleware composition order (outermost = telemetry per the comment in AgentTelemetryMiddleware.cs), (e) the ChatMessage namespace alias gotcha</step>
    <step>Read AnalysisQueryTools.cs + WebSearchTools.cs. Inventory: (a) how tools are registered (AIFunctionFactory.Create with [Description] attributes?), (b) parameter types, (c) how citation context threads through tool execution</step>
    <step>Read IAiToolHandler.cs + AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs. Identify the boundary between Agent Framework tools (chat-time, IChatClient-bound) and the AI Tool Framework (IAiToolHandler — analysis-time, orchestration-driven)</step>
    <step>Read ADR-013 + bff-extensions.md to capture the binding rules: PublicContracts/ facade requirement, BFF-extension governance, the categorical "no separate AI microservice unless 4 criteria met" rule</step>
    <step>Draft §1 (How this fits Spaarke's architecture) — sections: (a) Agent Framework's place in the BFF (chat surface, in-process, IChatClient-bound) vs. JPS-driven multi-step orchestration (AnalysisOrchestrationService), (b) When to use Agent Framework agents vs. Foundry Agent Service (lifetime + durability + HITL + A2A criteria), (c) Intersection with the AI Tool Framework (IAiToolHandler — keep the seam clear: chat-time IChatClient tools vs analysis-time AiToolHandler), (d) Hosting model: in-process only; ADR-001 prohibits Functions for new AI work; durability deferred to Foundry Agent Service</step>
    <step>Draft §2 (How we build with it) — sections: (a) Tool definition idioms (AIFunctionFactory.Create + [Description] — cite the Tools/*.cs files), (b) Middleware composition order (outermost = telemetry; cite AgentTelemetryMiddleware.cs lines 22-24), (c) The UseFunctionInvocation vs raw-client split for compound intent detection (cite SprkChatAgent.cs lines 60-69 + CompoundIntentDetector.cs), (d) Namespace alias gotcha (cite SprkChatAgent.cs lines 5-10 — `using AiChatMessage = Microsoft.Extensions.AI.ChatMessage`), (e) Streaming response handling (IAsyncEnumerable&lt;ChatResponseUpdate&gt;), (f) OTel + Application Insights wiring (where does the source-name come from, how does it line up with Sprk.Bff.Api's existing OTel pipeline), (g) Credential choice in production (ManagedIdentityCredential over DefaultAzureCredential per ADR-028 + upstream warnings — cite the providers.md upstream caveat), (h) Code review checklist (5-10 items targeting common drift — e.g., "must use AiChatMessage alias when both Models.Ai.Chat and Microsoft.Extensions.AI are imported")</step>
    <step>Verify every file path cited in NOTES.md resolves (Glob each path)</step>
    <step>If both §1 and §2 have substantive content: remove the `⚠️ STUB — senior engineer review pending` banner at the top. If any section is still TODO-only, keep the banner and mark NOTES.md as still-stub</step>
    <step>Write the new NOTES.md to knowledge/agent-framework/NOTES.md</step>
    <step>Commit: `docs(knowledge): rewrite agent-framework NOTES.md with Spaarke-grounded commentary (R1 task 007)`</step>
  </steps>
